explanation: We use two heaps, a max heap and a min heap, to efficiently maintain the median. The max heap stores the smaller half of the numbers, and the min heap stores the larger half. We add numbers to the heaps based on their values, and rebalance the heaps when necessary. The findMedian function returns the median by taking the average of the top elements of the two heaps when the size is even, or the top element of the max heap when the size is odd.

